## [![](iconsymbols/home.svg)](index.html)

This is the symbol for the square root of three

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/root3symbol.svg)

We use the square root of three to create an equilateral triangle which is symmetric around our starting point.  

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/trianglespelling.svg)

We break down the symbol glyphs into these rotations based on symmetries:

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/right30.svg)

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/right120.svg)

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/filled-equilateral-spelling.svg)


This is how we create the 120 degree isosceles triangle with Geometron:

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/cardboard-gnomon-spelling.svg)

Now we build a language.  We start with a symbol which represents drawing an equilateral triangle centered at the starting point.

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/triangle-shape.svg)

Then we can use a shrink action before the triangle and a grow action after to create a shrunken triangular tile centered on our starting point.  

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/shrunk-triangle-shape.svg)


Triangles are combined to create hexagons:

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/hexagonspelling.svg)

Hexagons are combined to make a unit cell:

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/hex-megacell-spelling.svg)

And these can be stacked to create a full symbol with several layers of sub-shape.


![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/cell-stack-spelling.svg)

Here are the keyboard values for the Geometron keyboard, mark them on your keys.

Try it out at  [symbol.html](symbol.html)

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/qwerty.svg)

![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/asdf.svg)


![](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LafeLabs/geometronmagic/main/hex/symbolfeed/colors.svg)



